You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for gist operations.

GIST COMMANDS
  clone:       Clone a gist locally
  create:      Create a new gist
  delete:      Delete a gist
  edit:        Edit a gist
  list:        List gists
  view:        View a gist


Note: These commands operate on your GitHub gists globally and do not require the --repo flag.

Example usage:
- Create gist: GH_PAGER="" gh gist create <file>
- List gists: GH_PAGER="" gh gist list
- View gist: GH_PAGER="" gh gist view <id> 